  "prompt": "How many offices does Google have around the world?  Which countries are they in?",
  "response": "Google has numerous offices around the world. As of my last update, Google has offices in over 50 countries. Here is a list of some of the countries where Google has offices:\n\n1. **United States**\n2. **Canada**\n3. **Mexico**\n4. **Brazil**\n5. **Argentina**\n6. **Chile**\n7. **Colombia**\n8. **Peru**\n9. **United Kingdom**\n10. **Ireland**\n11. **France**\n12. **Germany**\n13. **Italy**\n14. **Spain**\n15. **Netherlands**\n16. **Belgium**\n17. **Sweden**\n18. **Denmark**\n19. **Norway**\n20. **Finland**\n21. **Switzerland**\n22. **Austria**\n23. **Poland**\n24. **Russia**\n25. **Czech Republic**\n26. **Hungary**\n27. **Turkey**\n28. **Israel**\n29. **United Arab Emirates**\n30. **South Africa**\n31. **India**\n32. **China**\n33. **Japan**\n34. **South Korea**\n35. **Australia**\n36. **New Zealand**\n37. **Singapore**\n38. **Indonesia**\n39. **Malaysia**\n40. **Thailand**\n41. **Philippines**\n42. **Vietnam**\n43. **Hong Kong**\n44. **Taiwan**\n45. **Nigeria**\n46. **Kenya**\n47. **Ghana**\n48. **Egypt**\n49. **Saudi Arabia**\n50. **Ukraine**\n\nPlease note that the exact number of offices and their locations can change over time, so it's always a good idea to check Google's official website for the most current information.",
